阿.meaning: prefix to names of people to form terms of endearment

胞.meaning: the afterbirth; born of the same parents

呸.meaning: an onomatopoeic word; spit (out of disgust)

拼.meaning: piece together; spell; go all out

秦.meaning: an ancient state and dynasty name, Qin

喔.meaning: an onomatopoeic word (crowing of a cock), crow

隻.meaning: only, single; measure word for small animals

子.meaning: son; child; suffix for small objects
